Package com.algorand.algosdk.transaction

Class Transaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.algorand.algosdk.transaction.Transaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class Transaction
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A raw serializable transaction class, used to generate transactions to broadcast to the network. This is distinct from algod.model.Transaction, which is only returned for GET requests to algod.
    See Also:

        Create an asset creation transaction. Note can be null. manager, reserve, freeze, and clawback can be zeroed.
        Parameters:
        sender - source address
        fee - transaction fee
        firstValid - first valid round
        lastValid - last valid round
        note - optional note field (can be null)
        genesisID -
        genesisHash -
        assetTotal - total asset issuance
        defaultFrozen - whether accounts have this asset frozen by default
        assetUnitName - name of unit of the asset
        assetName - name of the asset
        url - where more information about the asset can be retrieved
        metadataHash - specifies a commitment to some unspecified asset metadata. The format of this metadata is up to the application
        manager - account which can reconfigure the asset
        reserve - account whose asset holdings count as non-minted
        freeze - account which can freeze or unfreeze holder accounts
        clawback - account which can issue clawbacks against holder accounts

      • createAssetTransferTransaction

        public static Transaction createAssetTransferTransaction​(Address assetSender,
                                                         Address assetReceiver,
                                                         Address assetCloseTo,
                                                         BigInteger assetAmount,
                                                         BigInteger flatFee,
                                                         BigInteger firstRound,
                                                         BigInteger lastRound,
                                                         byte[] note,
                                                         String genesisID,
                                                         Digest genesisHash,
                                                         BigInteger assetIndex)
        Creates a tx for sending some asset from an asset holder to another user. The asset receiver must have marked itself as willing to accept the asset.
        Parameters:
        assetSender - is a checksummed, human-readable address that will send the transaction and assets
        assetReceiver - is a checksummed, human-readable address what will receive the assets
        assetCloseTo - is a checksummed, human-readable address that behaves as a close-to address for the asset transaction; the remaining assets not sent to assetReceiver will be sent to assetCloseTo. Leave blank for no close-to behavior.
        assetAmount - is the number of assets to send
        flatFee - is the transaction flat fee
        firstRound - is the first round this txn is valid (txn semantics unrelated to asset management)
        lastRound - is the last round this txn is valid
        note -
        genesisID - corresponds to the id of the network
        genesisHash - corresponds to the base64-encoded hash of the genesis of the network
        assetIndex - is the asset index

      • setLease

        public void setLease​(byte[] lease)
        Lease enforces mutual exclusion of transactions. If this field is nonzero, then once the transaction is confirmed, it acquires the lease identified by the (Sender, Lease) pair of the transaction until the LastValid round passes. While this transaction possesses the lease, no other transaction specifying this lease can be confirmed. The Size is fixed at 32 bytes.
        Parameters:
        lease - 32 byte lease
